Patch Set 4:

Hi Zhi Yan

How would you feel about breaking this change apart into multiple commits? There are three significant parts I see: adding the policy checks (looks great!), the behavior change to images where they iterate through locations to find the first store that works when downloading data (looks great), and the PATCH support (I still need some more time to review this part).

I will immediately begin looking at the PATCH support portion, but wanted to go ahead and write this message first.
Uploaded patch set 5.

Patch Set 5:

Hey markwash, I have separate this patch to three.

1. This one, cover PATCH APIs changes to adding multiple locations support.
2. Adding multiple locations support to image downloading: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/35734/
3. Adding a policy layer for locations APIs: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/35741/

I don't suppose you'd care I create two additional BPs to cover separate patchs (#2, #3), right? ;)

Thanks!

2. locking protect/concurrent  control for the image status updating.
